# CRM Application - User Journeys

## 1. User Journey Overview
This document outlines the key user journeys for both Admin and Sales users in the CRM system. Each journey represents a common workflow that users will follow to accomplish their tasks.

## 2. Admin User Journeys

### 2.1 Initial System Setup Journey
1. **System Access**
   - Log into the system using admin credentials
   - Navigate to Settings > System Settings
   - Configure basic system parameters (company info, branding)

2. **User Management Setup**
   - Navigate to Settings > User Management
   - Create user accounts for team members
   - Assign appropriate roles (Admin/Sales)
   - Set initial permissions

3. **Data Structure Setup**
   - Configure custom fields for contacts if needed
   - Set up deal stages and pipeline structure
   - Define communication types and categories

4. **Success Metrics**
   - System configured according to business needs
   - User accounts created and roles assigned
   - Basic data structure ready for use

### 2.2 Ongoing System Management Journey
1. **Daily Monitoring**
   - Review dashboard for system performance
   - Check user activity logs
   - Monitor data integrity and duplicates

2. **User Support**
   - Handle user access issues
   - Process new user requests
   - Update user permissions as needed

3. **Data Management**
   - Oversee data import/export processes
   - Manage bulk updates when needed
   - Ensure data quality and consistency

4. **Success Metrics**
   - System running smoothly
   - User issues resolved promptly
   - Data maintained accurately

### 2.3 Reporting & Analysis Journey
1. **Report Generation**
   - Access Reports & Analytics section
   - Generate system-wide performance reports
   - Create custom reports as needed

2. **Performance Analysis**
   - Review sales team performance metrics
   - Analyze conversion rates and pipeline health
   - Identify trends and patterns

3. **Insights Communication**
   - Share relevant reports with stakeholders
   - Provide actionable insights to teams
   - Make data-driven recommendations

4. **Success Metrics**
   - Accurate reports generated
   - Clear insights identified
   - Effective communication of findings

## 3. Sales User Journeys

### 3.1 Contact Management Journey
1. **Contact Creation**
   - Navigate to Contacts > Add Contact
   - Enter required contact information
   - Add additional details and preferences
   - Save and verify contact details

2. **Contact Maintenance**
   - Regular review of assigned contacts
   - Update contact information as needed
   - Add notes and communication records
   - Track interactions and preferences

3. **Contact Organization**
   - Tag and categorize contacts
   - Set follow-up reminders
   - Maintain communication history

4. **Success Metrics**
   - Accurate contact records maintained
   - Regular updates logged
   - Effective contact organization

### 3.2 Deal Pipeline Journey
1. **Deal Creation**
   - Navigate to Deals > Add Deal
   - Select or create associated contact
   - Enter deal details and value
   - Set initial pipeline stage

2. **Deal Progression**
   - Update deal stages as they progress
   - Log activities and communications
   - Set tasks and reminders
   - Update probability and value estimates

3. **Deal Closure**
   - Move deals to Closed-Won or Closed-Lost
   - Document reason for closure
   - Update final deal value
   - Plan follow-up actions

4. **Success Metrics**
   - Deals properly tracked through pipeline
   - Regular updates maintained
   - Accurate closure documentation

### 3.3 Daily Operations Journey
1. **Morning Review**
   - Check dashboard for overview
   - Review tasks and reminders
   - Plan daily activities

2. **Activity Management**
   - Log new communications
   - Update deal statuses
   - Complete pending tasks
   - Schedule follow-ups

3. **End of Day**
   - Update remaining tasks
   - Plan next day's activities
   - Review performance metrics

4. **Success Metrics**
   - All activities logged
   - Tasks completed or rescheduled
   - Clear plan for next day

## 4. Integration Points

### 4.1 Admin-Sales Integration
- Admin users can view and assist with sales user activities
- Sales users can escalate issues to admin users
- Both roles contribute to system effectiveness

### 4.2 Cross-Role Communication
- Clear hierarchy for support requests
- Defined processes for data access requests
- Collaborative approach to system improvement

## 5. Success Factors
- **User Adoption**: Both admin and sales users actively using the system
- **Data Quality**: Consistent, accurate data entry across all journeys
- **Efficiency**: Streamlined workflows reducing time spent on administrative tasks
- **Effectiveness**: Improved customer relationships and sales outcomes
- **Scalability**: Journeys that can accommodate growing user base and data volume

